# skyline-timelapse — sample runtime config
#
# SCOPE OF THIS FILE
# ------------------
# This file is intended for **demo, local testing, and first-boot bring-up only**.
# A flat env file on disk is the simplest thing that works, but it is not a
# durable answer for production-grade secret hygiene.
#
# For real deployments, source these values from a proper secrets manager:
#   - HashiCorp Vault / OpenBao
#   - Doppler / Infisical
#   - 1Password Connect
#   - AWS Secrets Manager / GCP Secret Manager / Azure Key Vault
#   - sops-encrypted files in Git, decrypted at deploy time
#
# That said: even when using a secrets manager, the values listed in THIS file
# are non-sensitive operational config — bucket name, lat/lon, fps, retention.
# The actually-sensitive material (R2 access key + secret, RTSP credentials if
# embedded in URL) lives elsewhere:
#   - rclone config (~/.config/rclone/rclone.conf, mode 0600), OR
#   - a secrets manager that injects them at service start.
#
# Never commit a populated copy of this file. The repo ships the example only.
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# RTSP source — Protect stream URL for the rooftop camera.
# Swap to the DSLR-LD later by changing only this line.
RTSP_URL=

# Capture cadence and playback fps
CAPTURE_INTERVAL_SEC=60
OUTPUT_FPS=24

# Daylight gate location (default: Houston / EaDo)
LAT=29.749
LON=-95.34
TZ=America/Chicago
DAWN_BUFFER_MIN=15
DUSK_BUFFER_MIN=30

# R2 publishing
R2_REMOTE=r2
R2_BUCKET=
RETAIN_DAYS=30

# Working dirs (will be created if missing)
FRAME_DIR=/var/lib/timelapse/frames
OUT_DIR=/var/lib/timelapse/out
LOCK_FILE=/var/lock/timelapse-capture.lock
